sect1.para:
Healthcare organizations are structurally designed systems that are built with the intent to provide healthcare services in designated locations with varied populations. Healthcare organizations can include a physician group practice associated with a hospital system, clinics, hospitals, a host of different types of healthcare disciplines (e.g., nurses, physical therapists, respiratory therapists, physicians, etc.), third-party payers, the insured, specialty boards, and medical specialty groups (Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality, 
   2023
). Additional services provided by healthcare organizations are home care, subacute care (e.g., skilled nursing facilities), acute care, hospice, and palliative care.
